# Supabase (HalalScan)

Architecture: [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md). App mirror: `lib/services/product_service.dart`, `lib/services/keyword_service.dart`.

## Edge function (`lookup-product`)

- Entry: [`supabase/functions/lookup-product/index.ts`](../../supabase/functions/lookup-product/index.ts)
- **Verdict pipeline (source of truth):** [`VERDICT_PIPELINE.md`](../../supabase/functions/lookup-product/VERDICT_PIPELINE.md) — update when changing step order, skip logic, or post-rules in [`verdictRules.ts`](../../supabase/functions/lookup-product/verdictRules.ts) or request flow in `index.ts`.
- **Keyword safety override** after AI must stay intact (same invariant as the Flutter app).
- Built-in keyword lists: [`keyword.ts`](../../supabase/functions/lookup-product/keyword.ts) — keep aligned with app constants when changing haram/suspicious terms.
- Deno tests: `deno test --allow-env supabase/functions/lookup-product/verdictRules_test.ts`
- After function changes: redeploy `lookup-product` (see `.github/workflows/deploy-supabase.yml`).

## AI defaults (production)

This repo keeps **Claude off** by default (`CLAUDE_ENABLED=false`; no `CLAUDE_API_KEY` required). Lookup must still work via Open Food Facts + keywords. Gemini is optional (`GEMINI_*`). Details: [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md).

When testing AI paths locally: `supabase/.env.local` from `supabase/.env.e2e.example` — **gitignored**, never commit secrets.

## Migrations

- Add SQL under [`supabase/migrations/`](../../supabase/migrations/) with timestamp prefix `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`.
- Apply to test project and local E2E (`supabase db reset`) before relying on new columns/RLS.
- Schema for barcode cache: `products`, `product_analysis`, view `products_full` (see README → Development).

## Deno / TypeScript

- Use existing modules (`fetch.ts`, `db.ts`, `ai.ts`, `community.ts`) — match patterns in `lookup-product/`.
- CORS and JSON error responses follow `index.ts` conventions.
